RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 92. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE AUGUST 1 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Claiming And Starter Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).

CLAIM.OWNER: Bellasis, Tim and Tschanz, Cassandra A.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GALLANT WARREN tracked the decent early pace from the inside, was well positioned through the backstretch run, gained ground along the far turn, tipped two wide for the drive, overtook ROISTER inside of the furlong pole, was kept to task into the final sixteenth, felt pressure from oncoming rivals into deep stretch, was all out in the final yards and lasted for the win at the finish. TEX HANLEY broke a step slowly, was caught in early traffic and settled outside of runners into the first turn, improved position along the far turn while four wide, was roused three wide into the stretch, chased to the furlong grounds, responded to steady urging and rallied in deep stretch, pressured the winner to the finish but could not get by GALLANT WARREN and just missed for the win, while just holding for second. BROKEN FINGER was allowed to settle, raced inside of a rival while toward the back through the backstretch run, was steered to the three path along the far turn and came four wide into the stretch, finished well while racing widest into the final sixteenth and just missed for the win and place, while holding safely for the show. ROISTER was hustled leaving the start, assumed command and cleared the field into the first turn, dictated terms through the backstretch run, set a decent pace into the far turn and held a clear lead at the quarter marker, had the margin cut into in upper stretch, was overtaken by his stablemate inside of the furlong marker, chased GALLANT WARREN to deep stretch and weakened in the final sixteenth. GORDY'S BOY tracked the decent early pace while three wide, continued to track while outside of rivals through the backstretch run, chased three wide to the quarter marker, lost ground into the stretch and lacked a late rally. MY SUNSHINE was asked for early speed and was forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the decent pace from a two wide path through the backstretch run, lost position on the far turn, came three wide into the stretch and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Broken Finger
ENTRY.OWNER: Rivera Leobardo R and Sosa Manuela Franco

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 6F All Weather Track CR: 94. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $8,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SATANTA was unhurried in the early running, advanced while saving ground on the turn, was steered to the two path into upper stretch and was roused at the top of the lane, closed fast in mid-stretch and came within aim of YES HE CAN nearing the sixteenth-marker, caught the runner-up into deep stretch and inched away in the final stages. YES HE CAN was sent to establish the early lead, showed good speed while pressed into the turn, set quick fractions while pressed to the quarter marker, shook free into the stretch and drew to a clear lead inside of the furlong marker, was overtaken by the winner in deep stretch and bested the rest. REFI NOW tracked the quick early pace from the second flight, raced two wide along the turn and gained ground nearing the quarter marker, lost ground into the stretch, lacked the needed response in the final stages and was outkicked, while holding clearly in the end for third. R M C HOOK'EM tracked the quick early pace from the second flight, saved ground into the turn and improved position heading to the quarter marker, could not keep pace into the stretch and weakened in the final furlong. QUANTUM QUEST broke alertly, was asked to rate in the early stages but was a bit keen and pulled on the rider to press the solid early pace, pressed from the three path into the turn, kept pressure on the quick pace along the bend, lost position into the stretch, chased to the furlong marker and tired in the final stages.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 83. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIZ MY PRINCESS was allowed to settle leaving the break, raced outside of rivals into the backstretch run, improved position at the half-mile marker, was steered four wide into the second turn, loomed at the quarter marker and vied for the lead into upper stretch, battled with ZAFFERANA to the furlong marker, continued that duel approaching the sixteenth-pole, shook free into deep stretch and drew clear in the final stages. ZAFFERANA settled off of the solid early pace, raced outside of an inner rival into the backstretch run, improved position along the far turn, vied for the lead while three deep approaching the quarter marker, vied for the lead into upper stretch, battled with TIZ MY PRINCESS to the furlong marker, continued to battle into deep stretch, could not match strides with the winner in the final sixteenth and was outkicked, while besting the rest. HAPPY IS settled along the rail in the early stages, saved all of the ground to the far turn, angled out and came three wide into upper stretch, was not able to impact the top two in deep stretch and passed tired rivals in the final stages to secure third. CHIC SAMARAI tracked the solid early pace while closest to the leading pair, saved ground into the far turn, came in tight and waited for racing room nearing the top of the lane, tipped two wide for the stretch drive, ran evenly to mid-stretch and lacked a response in the final sixteenth. DANCING BONBON contested the early pace with MISSING PENNY then pressed the pace while outside of that rival, kept pressure on the solid fractions through the backstretch run, vied for the lead into the far turn and took a narrow advantage at the quarter marker, lost the lead into upper stretch, chased to the furlong marker and gave way in the final stages. MISSING PENNY was asked for speed leaving the start, contested the early lead with DANCING BONBON then assumed command into the first turn, set solid fractions while pressed through the backstretch run, lost the lead approaching the quarter marker, dropped back into upper stretch and tired in the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 1M All Weather Track CR: 94. Claiming Purse 17000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUGAR BEETS was unhurried in the early going, saved ground along the first turn then shifted to the two path into the backstretch, maintained that two wide path into the far turn, came three wide into the drive and loomed nearing mid-stretch, shifted out a path at the furlong marker and bumped HOWDOYALIKEMENOW, continued his long drive into the final sixteenth, vied for the lead with SPEED GRAZY in deep stretch, took command in the final yards and held in a drive at the finish to prevail. SPEED GRAZY settled off of the contentious early pace and saved ground into the first turn, saved ground while well placed through the backstretch run, saved all of the ground to the far turn, mounted an inside bid into upper stretch and took command nearing the furlong marker, was kept to task while under steady urging into deep stretch, was overtaken by SUGAR BEETS in the final strides and was outfinished for the win, while just holding for second at the finish. CANELITO was forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the decent early pace while outside of rivals and was well placed through the backstretch run, raced three wide into the far turn, came five wide into the stretch, moved out a path at the furlong grounds, rallied while widest in the late stages and just missed for second, while holding safely in the end for third. CHIEF WILD EAGLE raced close to the early pace leaving the break, took back along the first turn and tracked while four wide into the backstretch run, made a three wide middle move approaching the half-mile pole and attended to the decent pace into the far turn, vied for the lead while three wide nearing the quarter marker and battled into the stretch, fought for the lead with SPEED GRAZY at the furlong marker, continued into deep stretch, could not match strides with oncoming rivals in the final stages and tired late. HOWDOYALIKEMENOW was prominent in the early running, took back into the first turn and tracked the decent pace into the backstretch run, maintained a two wide path to the second turn, swung three wide for the drive and gained ground nearing mid-stretch, was bumped at the furlong marker by SUGAR BEETS and shifted to the four path at that station, could not keep pace with the leaders into deep stretch and weakened in the final stages. JOHNNY DAR was hard sent leaving the start, vied for the lead into the first turn then assumed command and showed the way into the backstretch run, set decent fractions while controlling the pace to the half-mile marker, showed the way into the far turn while off of the rail, came under pressure at the quarter marker, held foes at bay into upper stretch, battled for the lead to the furlong grounds and faded in deep stretch. THE RIDER OF HOWDOYALIKEMENOW LODGED AN OBJECTION AGAINST THE RIDER OF SUGAR BEETS FOR THE INCIDENT OCCURRING IN MID-STRETCH. IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE.

ENTRY.NAME: Johnny Dar
ENTRY.COMMENT: hard sent,set decent pace,off rail,battled upper stretch,faded

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 5 1M Turf CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CENTRE CIRCLE was forwardly placed in the early going, prompted the modest fractions through the backstretch, pressed the pace into the far turn then took a narrow lead at the quarter marker, battled between rivals into upper stretch, held a narrow lead at the furlong grounds, shook free into deep stretch, felt late pressure from oncoming rivals and determinedly kept to task in the final strides. GRACEFUL MISCHIEF was crowded at the start by an inner rival and was away a bit slowly, settled off of the modest early pace and raced two wide along the first turn, maintained that two wide path to the far turn while never far back, chased between rivals to the quarter marker, angled four wide for the stretch drive, gained ground at the furlong pole, closed in deep stretch, could not reel in the winner in the final stages and held well for second at the finish. MOONRISE DRIVE was bumped at the start by OUR NORTH STAR then raced a bit in traffic in the early stages, settled into the first turn and saved ground into the backstretch run, saved all of the ground to the far turn, was coaxed along to the outside and came five wide into the stretch, finished well inside of the furlong marker and just missed for second while getting up in time for third. THE SLAP was prominent leaving the start, rated into the first turn and tracked the pace from a three wide path into the backstretch run, was well positioned while outside of rivals heading to the half-mile marker, mounted a four wide bid along the far turn, vied for the lead into upper stretch, battled with CENTRE CIRCLE to the furlong grounds, could not sustain his run into the final sixteenth and flattened out late. TRIBUTE TO M paused at the start and was off very slowly, chased the field into the first turn, improved position at the half-mile marker and raced three wide into the far turn, swung six wide into the stretch and ran evenly to the furlong marker, was able to offer a mild late bid but needed more in deep stretch. BOBBED N LURED broke alertly and assumed command in the opening stages, set modest fractions while prompted into the backstretch run, carved out the pace while pressured to the half-mile marker, lost the lead to CENTRE CIRCLE along the far turn, fought back into upper stretch, could not match strides with the leaders into the final sixteenth and tired. OUR NORTH STAR broke out at the start and bumped with MOONRISE DRIVE, stalked the modest pace from the inside, saved all of the ground to the far turn, lost position into the stretch and gave way. BANOG BOY crowded GRACEFUL MISCHIEF at the start, pulled on the rider in the early going and rushed up to stalk three wide into the first turn, stalked the modest pace while outside of rivals along the backstretch run, lost position while three wide on the far turn, trailed into the stretch and could not muster a late response.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 1M All Weather Track CR: 97. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 31000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In Northern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs., Unless Entered for the Optional Claiming Price.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VANTAGE POINT hustled to the front, gained the rail and took short lead going into the clubhouse turn, slowed the pace down for the backstretch run, responded when asked to quicken away past the seven sixteenths pole, extended the lead, came into the stretch with plenty in reserve and outsprinted the field to the wire. ECOLOGIST broke slowly, spotted the field a head start, remained in the clear four wide, gradually regained contact with the field, swung into the stretch while still four wide and produced a strong rally to gain the place. MOOGIE SON raced close up while in the three path in the early going, went after the pacesetter approaching the three furlong marker, ran on well down the stretch under intermittent urging but could not reel in the eventual winner and was passed late for second. BUENISIMO was allowed to settle mid-pack while pulling on the rider through the first turn, settled into a tracking spot down the backstretch, came under a ride from the five-sixteenths pole but could not muster a rally and finished one-paced. CUT ACROSS SHORTY was not asked for speed from the gate, took the rail path to the far turn, tried to mount a rally with three furlongs to run but could not make an impact. TRINIDAD broke well and was pushed to gain forward position took a stalking position behind the leader and maintained that position to the far turn while under some restraint, was unable to keep pace when VANTAGE POINT quickened away, came under heavy pressure near the quarter pole then tired down the stretch.

Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since July 15 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ENOS SLAUGHTER tracked from mid-pack through the early stages, always traveling well in the clear to the outside, improved position from the half mile pole, was roused in earnest passing the quarter pole, had a clear run into the stretch, made a determined run, wore down QUE SERA SIR RALPH inside the final sixteenth then held off a fast closing rival at the wire. RESPECT THE HUSTLE tracked the early pace while keeping to the inside, attempted to launch a bid in the far turn but was stuck behind horses until the field turned for home, found a seam in deep stretch and surged to gain the place. QUE SERA SIR RALPH broke well then easily established a clear lead setting comfortable fractions in hand, took on a challenge from GROWTH ENGINE passing the three furlong marker, bested that one by mid-stretch, ran on gamely but could not hold off the top pair in the late stages. SEA OF LIBERTY tracked three deep to the half mile marker, launched a three wide bid on the far turn, drifted out a bit turning for home then ran on well despite drifting in and out a bit and just missed a minor award. HOUSE OF LORDS lagged near the back of the field, saved ground through the far turn, swung five wide into the stretch and made a good late run but could not make up the needed ground. RIJEKA (IRE) raced near the back of the field two deep to the far turn, began a mild rally with three furlongs to run, swung three wide for the stretch run, briefly encountered some traffic then found some room to run on the inside and ran on well in the final furlong. GROWTH ENGINE broke well and pressed QUE SERA SIR RALPH in the early stages, backed out near the seven-eighths marker and settled in to a stalking position two back, moved to challenge for the lead passing the three furlong pole, was rebuffed then tired in the stretch. RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 97. Starter Allowance Purse 22000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 15 Allowed 2 lbs. (One win for $25,000 or less will n ot be considered when determining eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIR GREYSON was asked for speed away from the gate, took back in the opening furlong and tracked the fast pace into the turn, gave chase while two wide approaching the quarter pole, overtook GOLDENSUNRISE in upper stretch and took command heading to the furlong marker, drew clear while kept to steady urging into deep stretch and powered home late as much the best. I'M DR. O settled off of the fast early pace, tracked the quick fractions while three wide into the turn and improved position at the quarter marker, loomed into upper stretch, raced on the left lead into the final sixteenth, was no match for the winner in the late stages and was second best. HYDRO FROST rated off of the fast early pace and saved ground into the turn, checked while in tight quarters at the three-furlong marker, chased from the rail to the quarter pole, angled five wide into upper stretch and advanced at the furlong marker, was not able to impact the top two in the final stages and held clearly at the end for third. GOLDENSUNRISE broke alertly and was hard sent in the early running, set a fast early pace and drew to a clear lead heading into the turn, carved out quick fractions from the rail heading to the quarter pole, was collared by SIR GREYSON in upper stretch, chased that rival to the sixteenth-marker and faded in deep stretch. WESTERN CAPE was away in good order, lacked early speed and chased the fast pace from the rear, was guided outside of rivals and came three wide to the quarter marker, swung six wide for the stretch drive, and did not threaten. MISCHIEVOUS PIRATE was squeezed at the start and was away a bit slowly, tracked the fast early pace while two wide and between runners, maintained that two wide path while between rivals into upper stretch, could not keep pace into the drive and did not factor in the final furlong. DINOS DIXIE tracked the fast early pace from the inside, lost position heading to the quarter marker, tipped two wide for the stretch drive, ran evenly to the furlong grounds and tired in the final stages.
